On Tue, 25 Oct 2005, Richard wrote:

> When I replaced mine I also went down the SS bolt route. What I did find was
> hex heads were about 1/2 the price of socket head caps and an added bonus was
> the bearing surface was a little larger to give more support on the tin (I
> still used washers)

Keep in mind that Stainless Steel doesn't mean no corrosion.  In fact, in
contact with some metals stainless can even promote corrosion!  I'm not
sure about the head material, but the captive nuts in the tin should be
OK.  In any case, a smidge of antisieze would be a good idea even with SS.

George
